<tr>
<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' width='80%' colSpan='4' bgcolor='#000000' class='header'><img border='0' src='./images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> DEFINING THE PALADIN</td>
</tr>
<tr> 
<td width='80%'><p align="left">Greetings Brothers and Sisters In Arms,</p>
<p align="left">I am writing this letter to you in the hope that the role of the
Paladin in Norrath is laid out to you in greater detail so that you may
understand our ways.</p>
<p align="left">I have been a Paladin for a great number of years now and feel
that some may have lost the Way.</p>
<p align="left">One must understand the role a Paladin plays and the Beliefs
They possess when presented with a problem or foe They must defeat. Ours is not
an easy task. We bring Justice and Honour to our foes with blade and hammer. The
use of ranged weapons or spells cast from a distance is an insult to Our
Abilities and Our Testament to the Destruction of Evil in Norrath. Our Skills
are granted to Us by the Righteousness of our Task and the Deity that grants us
that Right. As you look upon a battle and watch the Wizards spurt fire from
their fingers, and the Warriors loose their arrows, know that, while they are
important elements of Our Battles, We carry the day by destroying the Evil with
our own hands.</p>
<p align="left">We do not fight with two blades. This would lessen the Power of
Our Truthfulness. Every time we strike with Our blade, We are Cleansing the
Land. To fight with two blades would lessen our Resolve. Our Holy Brothers,
Clerics, refuse to use blades, rather fighting with blunted weapons, to lessen
damage and live to their vow of refusing to draw blood. We too, fight with
blunted weapons, but, on the whole, prefer to deal damage with Our Blades as the
drawing of blood ensures Our Evil Foes Destruction.</p>
<p align="left">Remember friends, Paladins have existed throughout the Ages. As
we arrived in Norrath, We did not expect to change Our Ways, nor should We.</p>
<p align="left">We must not be proud, nor be humble. Pride is a weakness,
causing many to die needlessly, many to falter. Humility would lessen Our
Resolve, for it takes away Our Confidence. We must not Judge. Evil will always
present itself, do not look for it, for it will find you. When Evil has
presented itself, slay it and Cleanse the Land! Remember, the Heart contains a
Creatures Evil. Although a Creature may appear Evil on the outside, look for it
Truthfully from the Heart.</p>
<p align="left">Through our Service and Truthfulness, the Gods have granted us
the use of Spells and Healing. To cast offensively would not be part of Our True
Being. When We are faced with Undead, they Cringe at Our Holiness and Fear our
Wrath. We rid the Land of Undead through the use of Our Holiness and Destructive
Power. Remember, Undead Creatures have no Hearts. Their very existence is an
insult to Our Task.</p>
<p align="left">The Gods have also granted us the Exclusive Use of Holy Swords,
for, if any other than a Paladin were to lay their hands upon a Holy Sword,
their minds would be swallowed up by its power. Use these Swords with the utmost
of care. Earn your blades. I&nbsp;encourage you to enter the Depths and earn
your Holy Sword as you were meant to.</p>
<p align="left">I hope I have left thee with more Resolve. Remember, We are not
meant to go about our Tasks easily. Ours is the Road of Truthfulness. If it were
to come easily, We would not become Stronger through the Trials we face.</p>
<p align="left">Help thy Fellow Paladins, and Go in the Light,</p>
<p align="left">Varrus</p>
<p align="left">PS: I&nbsp;hope you enjoyed this letter. I DO&nbsp;feel that
Paladins should be granted a &quot;type&quot; of Direct Damage spell. But it
would not deal damage. Some sort of Taunting spell that would enrage the animal
to attack you would be within our beliefs. Getting creatures to attack you from
range is more of a gameplay issue than anything else. Why couldn't we yell at a
creature to get them to attack us? Maybe a spell called Enrage, that would have
the same range as the majority of Direct Damage spells and act like a Taunt
times 5 or 10? Undead Creatures that were &quot;blue&quot; should certainly
attack ANY&nbsp;Paladin that was within sight.</p>
</td>
</tr>
